using @ media query vs. linked css
@media=few big http requests
    example: "
    @media screen and (max-width: 400 px){
        body { backgroud-color: red;}
        }
        "

linked css=many small http requests

make sure you have img, embed, object, video {
    max-width: 100%
    }

    look at content to look at breakpoints:


flexbox: default is row, add flex-wrap:wrap to have it go to next line
