Grid based layout framework:
framework=collections of css classes that make layout easy to implement

responsive web pages:
 resolution of screen in pixels to ensure uniformity across all screens
 size of certain aspects changes as size of screen changes

look up flex-wrap:wrap:
it makes columns align next to each other if their width is defined

negative space: added using padding, margin
padding on inside, margin on outside

overflow: text can scroll: "overflow: auto"
overflow is useful for small area

media specific css:
"@media only screen and (max-width: 300px) {
    p {
    background-color: blue;
    display: none;"
    }
}

